  "body" : "<p>I have a problem running a query on my SQL DB.</p>\n\n<pre><code>String code = xyz123    \nString sql=\"SELECT a.ACode, b.BCod \n     FROM (b RIGHT JOIN c ON b.BCod = c.CCod) \n          INNER JOIN a ON c.à = a.ID \n     WHERE b.BCod=\"+code;\nSystem.out.println(sql);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This should give me a list of data.\nI think the problem is the field with accented character.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>c.à</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>If i run the same query on phpmyadmin it works fine.</p>\n\n<pre><code>SELECT a.ACode, b.BCod FROM (b RIGHT JOIN c ON b.BCod = c.CCod) INNER JOIN a ON c.à = a.ID WHERE b.BCod=\"xyz123\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This is the query i run on phpmyadmin that works fine. \nI need to make that work on Java.</p>\n"
